INT. CONTROL ROOM - DAY

Monitors flicker with static. HANA watches one intently.

HANA
(V.O.)
If you're hearing this, the mission already went sideways.

VOICE ON RADIO (O.S.)
Copy that. We see the signal.

HANA
(CONT'D)
Get to the extraction point. Don't wait for me.

INT. CONTROL ROOM - LATER

Hana still hasn't moved. The static resolves into a face on screen.

DIRECTOR MOSS (O.S.)
(over intercom)
Report to debriefing. Now.

HANA
(V.O.)
(overlapping)
There isn't time for that.

TECH #1
(to Tech #2)
Is she even listening to us?

TECH #2
Never does.
